[[include component:image-block
| name=https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/2/24/Temple_Square_1912_panorama.jpg
| caption=Nexus Forty-Four on the day of the EE-6460 disappearance event.
| width=700px
| align=center]]


**Identifier:** Extranormal Event-6460

**Event Class:** Pending-Cambyses

**Operations for Containment:** Unnecessary. EE-6460 itself has concluded and no similar event, so far as the Foundation is currently aware, has since resurfaced in Nexus Forty-Four.

As to improve relations with the Laputan state, the Foundation has pledged humanitarian aid to help recover losses caused by EE-6460. This initiative, headed by agent Lemieux, is ongoing. Department of External Affairs personnel are to consult Document 6460-Luther with appropriate clearance for further information.

**Description:** EE-6460 was an anomalous planar disturbance that caused the disappearance of several objects and persons in Nexus Forty-Four ("Flying Island of Laputa") on December 19th, 1887. It would seem the effects of EE-6460 were limited to the Nexus itself, though the reason for this is unknown. The disappearances were instantaneous, occurring at exactly 4:16 PM, with their victims entirely demanifesting from baseline reality[[footnote]]According to agents Lemieux and Roksolana, who were on a diplomatic mission in Laputa at the time of the event, items and persons subject to EE-6460 completely vanished, even if directly observed.[[/footnote]]. Casualties included:

* An estimated thirty-nine (39) civilian casualties (all Laputan citizens; no Foundation operatives).
* Two (2) notable members of Laputan nobility, now designated PoI-6460-A and PoI-6460-B[[footnote]]According to Laputan citizens interviewed by agents, the given names of these individuals were Piranhaargabli Capribligut and Pixbligarbl Argabligutoadie respectively.[[/footnote]].
* Several articles of Laputan paramagnetic levitation technology.
* A small piece of SCP-68AG ("The Grand Lodestone")[[footnote]]The primary "stabilizer" responsible for  sustaining Nexus Forty-Four's levitation. Its precise workings are poorly understood at this time.[[/footnote]]. Its removal led to a brief period of unpredictable and disruptive, albeit relatively minor, gravitational destabilizations across Nexus Forty-Four.
* An elaborate necklace comprised of the teeth of //eques malignus infernalis// (Greenlandic nuckelavee), previously personally belonging to queen Balnibarigoiis VI.
* Several seemingly random buildings and pieces of public infrastructure, resulting in considerable damage to urban centers. Even with the aid of the Foundation, Nexus Forty-Four has yet to fully rebuild.

It is unknown whether the victims of EE-6460 were entirely erased from baseline reality or somehow transported to an accessory plane of existence. Further research is pending.

